<li>What is the difference between a developer and a tester? Answer in 2 lines.</li>
Answer:- Developer: A developer writes, designs, and maintains the code to build software or applications and adds new features.
         Tester: A tester checks the software for bugs, errors, and performance issues to make sure it works correctly and meets the required quality before it is released.
         
